09:36 AM Defendant Dewayne V Wilson in court with attorney Katie B. Kegel.  Susan L. Opper appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Opper presents her recommendations for sentencing.  Atty. Kegel presents her recommendations for sentencing.  Defendant presents statements.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT 5:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

7 YEARS IMPRISONMENT - 
  -  4 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

If Revoked,
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

TERM OF PROBATION:  5 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Suprevision IF sentence imposed):  
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s ; 
No Use or Possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
Court recommends to DOJ to revoke the defendant for ANY drug related infraction.

BUY MONEY:  $960.00 payable to the Waukesha County Metro Drug Unit (to be paid as a condition of probation);  

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 12 MONTHS Total - Defendant to report to the Huber facility by 9:00 a.m. on 01/25/2020 - 
6 Months Huber with release for works search, work, AODA treatment and/or counseling and child care (Court will deem the defendant elligible for good time credit);
Last 6 Months Huber with same release conditions, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
